## Exciting News! 🎉  

Yesterday was a tough day, but it ended on a high note—I’m thrilled to share that after three weeks of hard work, I’ve been accepted into **Cybersecurity Cohort 8!**  

## First Day of Network+  

Today, we officially started **Network+**, and thanks to Mr. Darryl’s introduction to some key concepts, I felt well-prepared to dive in. It’s exciting to see everything coming together!  

### Concepts Reviewed  

#### 1.1 Network+ - Explaining Network Topologies  
- Understanding different network topologies (Star, Mesh, Bus, Ring, Hybrid)  
- Pros and cons of each topology and their use cases  

#### 1.2 Network+ - OSI Model Concepts  
- The **7 Layers**: Physical, Data Link, Network, Transport, Session, Presentation, Application  
- How data moves through the model and its relevance to troubleshooting  

#### 1.3 Network+ - SOHO Networks  
- Setting up **Small Office/Home Office (SOHO) networks**  
- Configuration of routers, wireless security settings, and firewall basics  

#### 1.4 Network+ - Troubleshooting Methodology  
- **The 7-Step Troubleshooting Process:** Identify, Theorize, Test, Plan, Implement, Verify, Document  
- Importance of **systematic troubleshooting** for network issues  

## Cybersecurity Luncheon at CAU  

After class, we attended a **Cybersecurity Luncheon at CAU**, where I had the opportunity to hear from a panel of professionals with diverse experiences and insights. Their advice on success in the field was invaluable, and it reinforced my motivation to keep pushing forward.  

## Self-Study with Udemy  

Another exciting development—we signed up for **Udemy!** 🎓  
I’m really happy about this because it means that while we’re off, I can **self-study and prepare myself for the next 8 weeks**. Having additional resources will help reinforce what we’re learning in class and keep me ahead of the game.  

